RDA Registry Label:
has related nomen of item
has nomen string
has category of nomen
has scheme of nomen
has context of use
Justification for Mapping: $a must be preceded by $c and these $c $a pairs are repeatable. Each $c $a pair represents a name from a taxonomic category that is associated with the item, so each $c $a pair should be minted as a nomen with a scheme of nomen $2 -- 2024-02-01 CP
Transformation Notes:
Mint a new nomen for each $c $a pair

[item] has related nomen of item [nomenIRI]
[nomenIRI] rdan:P80068 has nomen string [value of $a]
[nomenIRI] rdan:P80078 has category of nomen [value of $c]
[nomenIRI] rdan:P80069 has scheme of nomen [value of $2]
[nomenIRI] rdan:P80067 has context of use 'Taxonomic Identification'

has related nomen of item
has nomen string
has category of nomen
Transformation Notes:
Mint a new nomen for each $d

[item] has related nomen of item [nomenIRI]
[nomenIRI] rdan:P80068 has nomen string [value of $d]

RDA Registry Label: is item described with metadata by
Transformation Notes:
[itemIRI] is item described with metadata by [newly minted metadataIRI]
[metadataIRI] rdf:type rdf:statement
[metadataIRI] rdf:subject [itemIRI]
[metadataIRI] rdf:predicate [rdai:p40028 has note on item]
[metadataIRI] rdf:object ['Taxonomic identification note: ' + value of $x]
[metadataIRI] has category of work 'private'
